---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Nurses | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Nurses working internationally, covering nursing positions abroad, healthcare careers overseas, and global nursing opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Nurses";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Nurses working abroad, providing patient care internationally, and pursuing careers across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/nurse-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/nurse-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Nurse Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Nurses provide direct patient care, administer medications, coordinate treatments, and support patient recovery across healthcare settings. International nursing offers opportunities to work in diverse healthcare systems, gain varied clinical experience, and address global nursing shortages.
      </p>
      <p>
        International nursing opportunities exist through hospitals worldwide, international healthcare organizations, travel nursing agencies, and the significant global demand for qualified nursing professionals.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Nurses</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Infectious disease coverage', why: 'Patient exposure risks', typical: 'Essential for profession' },
          { need: 'Physical coverage', why: 'Patient handling and active care', typical: 'Important for profession' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Emotional demands of patient care', typical: 'Important for profession' },
          { need: 'Occupational injury', why: 'Healthcare workplace risks', typical: 'Employer typically provides' },
          { need: 'Back/musculoskeletal', why: 'Patient lifting and positioning', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Occupational Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        Nurses face occupational health risks including infectious disease exposure, needlestick injuries, and patient-related incidents. Comprehensive coverage including infectious disease protection is particularly important for nursing work. Healthcare employers typically provide occupational health coverage.
      </p>
      <p>
        Physical demands—patient lifting, prolonged standing, and emergency response—create musculoskeletal injury risks. Coverage supporting back and joint health helps sustain demanding nursing careers.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Patient care involves significant emotional labor—supporting patients and families through difficult experiences. Mental health support helps nurses manage the emotional demands of healthcare work, including compassion fatigue and burnout risks.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Hospital</h3>
      <p>
        Acute care nursing. Hospital benefits comprehensive. Shift work. Hospitals offer variety.
      </p>

      <h3>International Clinic</h3>
      <p>
        Outpatient or specialty clinic. Clinic benefits vary. Regular hours often. Clinics offer focus.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel Nursing</h3>
      <p>
        Assignment-based nursing. Agency benefits. Multiple locations. Travel nursing offers flexibility.
      </p>

      <h3>Humanitarian</h3>
      <p>
        NGO or humanitarian nursing. Organization benefits. Resource settings. Humanitarian offers impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Healthcare</h3>
      <p>
        Private hospital or clinic. Premium benefits often. Patient population specific. Private offers resources.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Nurses"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Nurse Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Nursing License</h3>
      <p>
        RN or equivalent. National nursing license. Licensure required for practice.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Verification</h3>
      <p>
        International credential recognition. Verification process. Country-specific requirements vary.
      </p>

      <h3>Specializations</h3>
      <p>
        Critical care, pediatrics, oncology. Specialty certifications. Advanced practice nursing.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Language proficiency. Patient communication. Documentation requirements. Language often required.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Exposure Risks</h3>
      <p>
        Infectious disease. Needlestick injuries. Patient contact. Exposure coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Patient handling. Extended standing. Emergency response. Physical coverage important.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Labor</h3>
      <p>
        Patient care intensity. Family support. End-of-life care. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Shift Work</h3>
      <p>
        Night shifts. Rotating schedules. Extended hours. Wellness support relevant.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Patient Care</h3>
      <p>
        Direct nursing care. Medication administration. Treatment coordination. Care is core work.
      </p>

      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>
        Patient assessment. Vital signs. Condition monitoring. Assessment guides care.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Care documentation. Medical records. Communication notes. Documentation ensures continuity.
      </p>

      <h3>Team Coordination</h3>
      <p>
        Physician collaboration. Healthcare team. Shift handoffs. Coordination ensures safety.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Nursing shortages worldwide. High demand profession. Immigration pathways often available. Opportunities abundant.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Charge nurse. Nurse manager. Clinical specialist. Nurse practitioner. Multiple advancement paths.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Credential recognition varies. Verification required. Some countries straightforward. Research destination requirements.
      </p>

      <h3>Salary Variation</h3>
      <p>
        Compensation varies significantly by country. Benefits packages differ. Consider total package value.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a nurse considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Credential verification required. Employers typically provide coverage. Demand high globally. Language may be required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do international employers provide health coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes typically. Hospital employers especially. Benefits quality varies. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is occupational health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for nursing. Exposure risks real. Physical demands significant. Occupational coverage essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do nursing credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Verification required. Process varies by country. Some straightforward, others complex. Research requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for patient care. Emotional demands high. Burnout risks real. Support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Global nursing shortage. High demand continues. Immigration pathways available. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Ensure occupational health coverage for exposure risks. Include mental health support for care demands. Research credential requirements for your destination.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nurses provide essential care worldwide. Your coverage should support nursing careers—addressing occupational demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across nursing work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Nursing Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Nurses working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
